<div id="t4-main-body" class="t4-section  t4-main-body  container"><div class="t4-section-inner container-fluid"><div class="t4-row row"><div class="t4-col component col-12 col-md-6 col-lg container"><div id="system-message-container" aria-live="polite"></div><div class="com-content-article item-page" ><div class="page-header"><h1 > Top 5 industries that need to register ESG in 2026 </h1></div><div class="ja-share-button" layout="default" ></div><dl class="article-info text-muted"> <dt class="article-info-term"> Details </dt><dd class="createdby" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/Person"> Written by: <a href="../../our-experts/author/duns-registration-experts.html" >Expert in DUNS registration</a> </dd> <span style="display: none;" itemprop="publisher" itemscope> <span >Expert in DUNS registration</span> <span itemprop="logo" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/ImageObject"> <img src="../../../templates/ja_alpha/images/logo.png" alt="logo" width="160" height="40"> <meta itemprop="width" content="auto" /><meta itemprop="height" content="auto" /></span> </span> <dd class="modified"> <span class="fa fa-calendar" aria-hidden="true"></span> <time datetime="2025-12-08T13:57:22+07:00" itemprop="dateModified"> Last Updated: 08 December 2025	</time> </dd> </dl><ul class="fields-container"> <li class="field-entry rating-count "> <span class="field-label ">Rating Count: </span> <span class="field-value ">79</span> </li> <li class="field-entry rating-value "> <span class="field-label ">Rating Value: </span> <span class="field-value ">4.9</span> </li></ul><div class="com-content-article__body"><p>The difference between thriving in a changing business landscape and falling behind?Â </p><p><a href="esg-registered-db.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Strategic ESG adoption</a></p><p>By aligning with ESG (Environmental, Social, and Governance) principles, businesses can unlock new growth opportunities, attract investors, and stay ahead of regulations.</p><p>Take the renewable energy sector, for example.</p><p>With billions in global investments and increasing consumer demand, companies in this space are thriving. But success isnâ€™t random.</p><p>They proactively integrate ESG strategiesâ€”ensuring sustainability, compliance, and long-term profitability.</p><p>Your business can, too. ESG isnâ€™t just a trend; itâ€™s a game-changer.</p><p>To help you navigate this shift, we have identified the top five business sectors that should prioritize ESG registration for long-term growth.</p><h2 class="indexed"><span id="top-5-business-sectors-that-should-prioritize-esg-registration" class="anchor"></span><span class="heading_number">1.</span> <span class="heading_text">Top 5 business sectors that should prioritize ESG registration</span></h2><p>After perusing key industry reports where ESG is not just beneficial, or required, but essential for long-term growth, investment opportunities, and competitive advantage.</p><p>Top 5 industries are renewable energy, wood export, Â agricultural export, manufacturing (fertilized, aluminium, steel, cement), and textile and fashion.</p><h3 class="indexed"><span id="renewable-energy-solar-wind-hydropower" class="anchor"></span><span class="heading_number">1.1.</span> <span class="heading_text">Renewable energy (Solar, Wind, Hydropower)</span></h3><p>With global efforts to achieve Net-Zero emissions by 2050, countries heavily invest in renewable energy sources like solar, wind, and hydropower.</p><p>ESG certification is a game-changer in this landscape, helping businesses in Singapore, Hong Kong, and the U.S. attract investors, expand into new markets, and strengthen their sustainability brand.</p><p>In short, ESG matters for renewable energy companies: because:Â </p><ul> <li>ESG-certified projects have better access to green investment funds;</li> <li>It helps meet sustainability standards required for partnerships in the EU and U.S;</li> <li>It shows that the companies are willing to demonstrate a commitment to long-term sustainable development.</li> </ul><h3 class="indexed"><span id="wood-export-and-processing" class="anchor"></span><span class="heading_number">1.2.</span> <span class="heading_text">Wood export and processing</span></h3><p>Strict regulations from the EU and U.S. are reshaping the wood export and processing industry. While these policies create challenges, they also open doors for businesses that meet sustainability standards.</p><p>By December 2025, the EU will <a href="https://environment.ec.europa.eu/topics/forests/deforestation/regulation-deforestation-free-products_en" target="_blank" rel="noopener">ban imports of wood products linked to deforestation</a>. Likewise, the U.S. Lacey Act requires all wood products to be legally sourced and sustainably produced.</p><p>With these rule implementations, ESG certification is more essential than ever for wood exportersÂ </p><ul> <li>ESG-certified wood is highly valued by importers and consumers, boosting product prices and profitability;</li> <li>Businesses with ESG certification can enter highly regulated markets like the EU and U.S. with fewer restrictions;</li> <li>ESG compliance demonstrates a commitment to sustainability, helping companies build a trusted and competitive brand.</li> </ul><h3 class="indexed"><span id="agricultural-exports" class="anchor"></span><span class="heading_number">1.3.</span> <span class="heading_text">Agricultural exports</span></h3><p>Agricultural export businesses face mounting pressure from regulations like the EU Deforestation-Free Law and strict traceability requirements. These policies ensure that exported goods meet sustainability and environmental standards.</p><ol> <li>Coffee, Rubber, Pepper, Cashew, Durian â€“ The company must provide full traceability and prove they are not linked to deforestation.</li> <li>Fruits &amp; Vegetables â€“ The produce must be subject to strict phytosanitary (plant health) and quarantine regulations.</li> </ol><p>To maintain and expand export markets, businesses must proactively adopt ESG standards.Â </p><p>Securing ESG certification can provide several advantages:</p><ul> <li>It positions your business as socially and environmentally responsible;</li> <li>It opens doors to highly regulated markets like the EU and U.S;</li> <li>It prevents supply chain disruptions.Â </li> </ul><p>For more information, you can check out the article here: <a href="esg-for-export-companies.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">How to get ESG registered D&amp;B certification for companies exporting to the EU.</a></p><h3 class="indexed"><span id="cement-steel-aluminium-and-fertilizer-industry" class="anchor"></span><span class="heading_number">1.4.</span> <span class="heading_text">Cement, steel, aluminium, and fertilizer industry</span></h3><p><a href="https://trade.ec.europa.eu/access-to-markets/en/news/carbon-border-adjustment-mechanism-cbam" target="_blank" rel="noopener">The EU Carbon Border Adjustment Mechanism</a> (CBAM) is increasing pressure on heavy industries such as cement, steel, aluminum, and fertilizer.Â </p><p>Since October 2023, CBAM requires importers to report carbon emissions and purchase carbon credits if their products fail to meet environmental standards.Â </p><p>The regulation is expected to expand further to cover organic chemicals, plastics, and ammonia.</p><p>To stay competitive, heavy industry players must transition to sustainable production models. ESG certification is a key step in this transformation.</p><ul> <li>Many investment funds now prioritize businesses that meet ESG criteria;</li> <li>It strengthens brand reputation with eco-friendly products and processes;</li> <li>It ensures seamless access to EU and U.S. markets with strict environmental standards.</li> </ul><p>For a detailed guide on obtaining ESG certification, you can check out our article here: <a href="esg-for-singapore-holding-company.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">How to register for ESG Certification for Holding companies</a>.</p><h3 class="indexed"><span id="textile-and-fashion-industry" class="anchor"></span><span class="heading_number">1.5.</span> <span class="heading_text">Textile and fashion industry</span></h3><p>The circular production trend is reshaping the global textile and fashion industry, with the EU leading efforts toward sustainability. Key regulations under the <a href="https://environment.ec.europa.eu/strategy/textiles-strategy_en" target="_blank" rel="noopener">EU Sustainable Textile Strategy</a> include:</p><p>Longer-lasting, repairable, and recyclable products â€“ Textile products must be durable, non-toxic, and environmentally friendly;</p><ul> <li>Full product lifecycle responsibility â€“ Manufacturers must take accountability for design, production, consumption, and waste management, limiting landfilling and incineration;</li> <li>Circular production model â€“ Transforming waste into new resources to promote recycling and reuse.</li> </ul><p>The EU is introducing new legal measures to enhance sustainability, including EPR (Extended Producer Responsibility) regulations for textiles. Consumers are also shifting toward high-quality, eco-friendly products, presenting both challenges and opportunities for businesses.</p><p>To stay competitive, textile companies must adopt sustainable production models. ESG certification is a key step in this transformation.</p><h2 class="indexed"><span id="how-can-we-help-you-stay-competitive-with-esg-registration" class="anchor"></span><span class="heading_number">2.</span> <span class="heading_text">How can we help you stay competitive with ESG registration?</span></h2><p>You need to align with sustainability standards. And to do that effectively, you need the right ESG certification strategy.</p><p>Whether you pursue ESG registration to meet regulatory requirements or to enhance your brandâ€™s value (or both), sustainability compliance can position your business for long-term success.</p><p>For best results, combine E